It's not possible to explicitly pass the `ExecutionContext` in for comprehensions
```scala
for {
  a <- foo()
} yield a + 2
```

ahh okay now I get what this `debuggingProvider` was for!

I moved it to where I create a list of lens providers. 
If debugging is off I only create `superMethodProvider` but if debugging is on I create both.

```scala
    val runTestLensesProvider: List[CodeLenses] = if (clientExperimentalCapabilities.debuggingProvider) {
      List(new RunTestLensesProvider(buildTargetClasses, buffers, buildTargets))
    } else {
      List.empty
    }
```
